    <h1>All About Bottles</h1>
    <p>A bottle is a container that is typically made of glass, plastic, or metal and is used to store and transport liquids such as water, juice, milk, and beer. Bottles can be made in a variety of shapes and sizes, and can be designed for different purposes, such as storage, transportation, or packaging.</p>
    <h2>Types of Bottles</h2>
    <p>There are many different types of bottles, including water bottles, soda bottles, beer bottles, and wine bottles. These bottles are typically made of materials such as glass, plastic, or metal, and are designed to hold specific types of liquids.</p>
    <p>Bottles are also used for packaging and storing other types of products, such as shampoo, lotion, and cleaning products. These bottles are often made of plastic and may have a pump or spray top for easy dispensing.</p>
    <h2>History of Bottles</h2>
    <p>Bottles have been used for centuries to store and transport liquids, and have played a significant role in the development of trade and commerce. Today, bottles are used in a wide range of industries, including food and beverage, cosmetics, and pharmaceuticals.</p>
